Detailed Syllabus of Artificial Intelligence

1. Foundations of AI

* History and Evolution of AI
* Definition and Scope of AI
* Applications of AI (Healthcare, Finance, Education, Robotics, NLP, Vision, etc.)
* Intelligent Agents and Environments
* Types of agents (reflex, goal-based, utility-based, learning agents)
* PEAS (Performance measure, Environment, Actuators, Sensors)

2. Problem Solving

* State-Space Search
* Problem formulation
* Uninformed search (DFS, BFS, Uniform Cost)
* Informed search (Greedy, A\*)
* Heuristic Search
* Hill climbing, Simulated Annealing, Genetic Algorithms
* Constraint Satisfaction Problems (CSPs)
* Backtracking, Local Search, Min-Conflicts

3. Knowledge Representation and Reasoning

* Propositional Logic and Predicate Logic
* Knowledge Representation Methods
* Semantic Networks, Frames, Ontologies
* Inference Mechanisms
* Forward and Backward Chaining, Resolution
* Uncertainty in AI
* Fuzzy Logic, Bayesian Networks, Hidden Markov Models

4. Machine Learning

* Supervised Learning
* Regression (Linear, Logistic, Polynomial)
* Classification (Decision Trees, Na√Øve Bayes, SVM, k-NN)
* Ensemble Learning (Random Forest, Gradient Boosting, XGBoost)
* Unsupervised Learning
* Clustering (k-Means, Hierarchical, DBSCAN)
* Dimensionality Reduction (PCA, t-SNE)
* Reinforcement Learning
* Markov Decision Processes, Q-Learning, SARSA, Policy Gradient Methods
* Model Evaluation: Accuracy, Precision, Recall, F1, ROC-AUC

5. Neural Networks and Deep Learning

* Basics of Artificial Neural Networks (ANNs)
* Activation Functions (Sigmoid, ReLU, Softmax)
* Deep Neural Networks (DNNs)
* Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs)
* Image classification, Object detection
* Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs)
* LSTMs, GRUs, Sequence prediction
* Generative Models
* GANs (Generative Adversarial Networks), Variational Autoencoders (VAEs)
* Transfer Learning and Fine-tuning (ResNet, VGG, BERT)

6. Natural Language Processing (NLP)

* Text Preprocessing (Tokenization, Lemmatization, Stop words, POS tagging)
* Word Embeddings (Word2Vec, GloVe, FastText)
* Transformers (BERT, GPT family)
* Sequence-to-Sequence Models
* Applications: Sentiment Analysis, Chatbots, Text Summarization, Question Answering

7. Computer Vision

* Image Preprocessing (Resizing, Normalization, Augmentation)
* CNN Architectures (LeNet, AlexNet, VGG, ResNet, Inception, EfficientNet)
* Object Detection (R-CNN, Fast R-CNN, YOLO, SSD)
* Image Segmentation (U-Net, Mask R-CNN)
* Applications: Face Recognition, Medical Imaging, OCR

8. Generative AI

* Prompt Engineering
* Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG)
* LangChain, LlamaIndex frameworks
* Fine-tuning Large Language Models (LLMs)
* Applications: AI Assistants, Resume Analyzer, AI Tutors

9. Robotics and AI Applications

* Path Planning (A\*, Dijkstra, RRT)
* Robot Perception and Localization
* Reinforcement Learning in Robotics
* Autonomous Vehicles

10. AI Ethics and Explainability

* Bias and Fairness in AI
* Transparency and Explainable AI (XAI)
* Adversarial Attacks in AI
* Responsible AI principles

11. AI Deployment and Tools

* Model Deployment (Flask, FastAPI, Streamlit)
* MLOps basics: CI/CD for ML, Docker, Kubernetes
* Cloud AI Services (AWS Sagemaker, GCP AI, Azure ML)
* Experiment Tracking (MLflow, DVC)

12. Research and Case Studies

* Latest AI Trends (Edge AI, Federated Learning, Multimodal AI)
* AI in Healthcare, Finance, Education, Cybersecurity, Agriculture
* Research Paper Writing and Implementation
